parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of critical systems, including the anti-lock braking system, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.

The failure of the sliding side door handles can cause difficulties in opening or closing the door, which can lead to inconvenience, especially in emergency situations. In some cases, it can also cause the door to break off or become stuck, posing a safety risk.
symptoms: the door is difficult to open or close
the interior light will not come on when the door is open.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Door Design and Safety Concerns

making it difficult or impossible to open the doors from the inside.
